title: Complementary Medicine (Alternative Medicine)
content: Complementary Medicine (Alternative Medicine) | Complementary medicine, also known as alternative medicine, refers to a variety of treatment methods that are not part of conventional medicine. These methods combine traditional and modern therapeutic approaches, focusing on holistic care for both body and mind. Health funds in Israel offer a range of complementary medicine treatments as part of their extended healthcare services.

title: Complementary Medicine (Alternative Medicine)
content: Complementary Medicine (Alternative Medicine) | The table below presents the main complementary medicine treatments offered by the health funds "Maccabi," "Meuhedet," and "Clalit," along with the benefits provided to insured members under the various insurance plans. The treatments include:

title: Complementary Medicine (Alternative Medicine)
content:
Complementary Medicine (Alternative Medicine) | Acupuncture: A treatment based on inserting thin needles into specific points on the body 
 Shiatsu: A Japanese massage technique that involves applying pressure to points along the body's energy pathways 
 Reflexology: A treatment based on massage and pressure applied to the feet 
 Naturopathy: A therapeutic approach combining nutrition, herbal medicine, and other natural methods 
 Homeopathy: A treatment method based on administering highly diluted substances 
 Chiropractic: Manual therapy for the skeletal and muscular systems, primarily the spine

title: Communication Clinics
content: Communication Clinics | Communication clinics specialize in diagnosing and treating communication, language, speech, and swallowing disorders. They provide comprehensive services for children and adults experiencing various communication difficulties. The clinic staff includes expert speech therapists who use advanced treatment methods and innovative technologies to improve patients' communication abilities.

 Stuttering treatment: Advanced methods to improve speech fluency 
 Treatment of voice disorders: Rehabilitation and improvement of voice quality 
 Diagnosis and treatment of swallowing disorders: Evaluation and treatment of swallowing difficulties 
 Developmental delay treatment: Early intervention for children with language delays 
 Hearing rehabilitation: Support for users of hearing aids and cochlear implants

title: Pregnancy
content: Pregnancy | The pregnancy period is a significant time in every woman's life, accompanied by numerous physical and emotional changes.  Treatment for pregnancy complications: Monitoring and treatment of special conditions

title: Dental Clinics
content: Dental Clinics | Dental clinics offer a wide range of oral health services, including routine check-ups, cleanings, fillings, root canal treatments, extractions, and cosmetic procedures. These clinics are staffed by licensed dentists and hygienists who use modern equipment to ensure quality care for patients of all ages.

title: Dental Clinics
content: Dental Clinics | The table below presents all the sub-services provided by dental clinics, along with the rates and benefits according to the insurance plans of the health funds "Maccabi," "Meuhedet," and "Clalit." The services include:

title: Dental Clinics
content:
Dental Clinics | Dental Check-ups and Cleanings: Periodic examinations and professional cleanings 
 Fillings: Treatment for cavities and tooth restoration 
 Root Canal Treatments: Treatment for infections and inflammation in tooth roots 
 Crowns and Implants: Restoration of damaged or missing teeth 
 Orthodontics: Treatments to improve teeth alignment and bite 
 Cosmetic Treatments: Teeth whitening, veneers, and aesthetic smile improvements

title: Dental Clinics
content: Dental Clinics | Each service is detailed with the benefits available for the Gold, Silver, and Bronze plans in each health fund.
